  <static seed="1293" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions170.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{x^{5}+9x^{4}+20x^{3}}{x^{5}-2x^{4}-24x^{3}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x+5}{x-6}, x\ne -4\hbox{ and }x\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{x^{5}+9x^{4}+20x^{3}}{x^{5}-2x^{4}-24x^{3}}} \amp = \frac{{x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+9x+20\right)}}{{x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}-2x-24\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}}{{x^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(x-6\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {\frac{x+5}{x-6}, x\ne -4\hbox{ and }x\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>x^{3}</m> and <m>x+4</m> were crossed out, the domain conditions lost during the simplification are <m>x \ne 0</m> and <m>x \ne -4</m>.</p>
</solution>
